---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Designing Distributed Systems That Scale</h1>
			<p>
				Welcome to <strong>{SITE_TITLE}</strong>, the technical blog of <strong>Rasheed Bustamam</strong>.
				I run <strong>Bustamam Technology</strong>, a consulting practice focused on designing, scaling,
				and evolving distributed systems. This space lives at
				<a href="https://blog.bustamam.tech" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> blog.bustamam.tech</a> and
				is dedicated to the real-world practice of distributed architecture.
			</p>
			<p>
				Here you'll find deep dives into distributed systems design, scalability, reliability, and
				operability—drawing from hands-on work with event-driven architectures, microservices, and
				cloud-native platforms. Posts focus on the trade-offs behind architecture decisions, not just
				the happy-path diagrams.
			</p>
			<p>Use this blog to:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Explore blog posts that break down distributed architecture patterns and anti-patterns.</li>
				<li>Learn how to reason about consistency, resilience, and performance in complex systems.</li>
				<li>
					Discover how Bustamam Technology approaches system design for teams that need to scale safely.
				</li>
				<li>
					Visit the main portfolio and services site at
					<a href="https://bustamam.tech" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> bustamam.tech</a> if you're
					looking for distributed architecture consulting or hands-on delivery help.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
